[[File:The Empire and Expeditions of Alexander the Great.png|thumb|The Empire and Expeditions of Alexander the Great by Félix Delamarche, 1833]]
'''Félix Delamarche''' was a [[France|French]] [[geographer]] and [[engineer]] who flourished during the 18th century and early 19th century.<ref name=geographicus>{{cite web|title=Charles Francois Delamarche, The Delamarche Family |url=http://www.geographicus.com/mm5/merchant.mvc?Screen=CAD&Product_Code=delamarche |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130727000802/http://www.geographicus.com/mm5/merchant.mvc?Screen=CAD&Product_Code=delamarche |dead-url=yes |archive-date=27 July 2013 |publisher=Geographicus |accessdate=26 July 2013 }}</ref><ref name=MG>{{cite web|title=Félix Delamarche|url=http://catalogue.museogalileo.it/biography/FelixDelamarche.html|work=Biography|publisher=Museo Galileo|accessdate=26 July 2013}}</ref>  His father was the map publisher [[Charles Francois Delamarche]].

Félix Delamarche became the owner of his father's map publishing company, Maison Delamarche. He ran the company alongside [[cartographer]] [[Charles Dien]]. The firm would eventually be passed down to Alexandre Delamarche.<ref name=geographicus/> Delamarche created ''Atlas de la géographie ancienne et moderne'' in 1820. The [[atlas]] was reprinted during the 19th century. It was utilized by the [[Ecole Spéciale Militaire de Saint-Cyr]]. His work is held in the collection of the [[Library of Congress]].<ref name="WDL">{{cite web |url = http://www.wdl.org/en/item/11738/ |title = The Empire and Expeditions of Alexander the Great |website = [[World Digital Library]] |year = 1833 |accessdate = 2013-07-26 }}</ref>

