{{Muisca sidebar}}
This is a '''list''' of '''museum collections''' pertaining to the '''Muisca'''. Most of the [[Muisca people|Muisca]] artefacts are housed in the [[Gold Museum, Bogotá]], the museum with the most [[gold]]en objects in the world. Other findings are in the [[Archaeology Museum, Sogamoso|Archaeology Museum]] in [[Sogamoso]] and in the [[Archeological Museum of Pasca|Archaeology Museum]] of [[Pasca]]. Few artefacts are on display outside [[Colombia]]. Most of the objects outside Colombia are ''[[tunjo]]s''; small offer pieces part of the [[Muisca religion]].
