ly Peruvian" [sic]</ref> |- | align=center | [[The Israel Museum]] | align=center | [[Jerusalem]] | align=center | [[Israel]] | align=center | 1 | align=center | pectoral | align=center | <ref>[http://www.imj.org.il/imagine/collections/item.asp?itemNum=534428 Muisca collection of The Israel Museum]</ref> |- | align=center | [[British Museum]] | align=center | [[London]] | align=center | [[United Kingdom]] | align=center | 2 | align=center | ''[[tunjo]]'' & [[Muisca mummification|mummy]] | align=center | <ref>[https://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/themes/lost_kingdoms_of_south_america/muisca_and_tairona.aspx Muisca collection of the British Museum]</ref><ref>{{cite LSA |last=Martínez Martín |first=Abel Fernando |last2=Martínez Santamaría |first2= Luz |year=2012 |title=Sobre la momificación y los cuerpos momificados de los muiscas - On mummification and the mummified bodies of the Muisca |journal=Revista Salud Historia Sanidad |series=7 |volume=1 |pages=61-80 |issn=1909-2407 |language=es}}</ref> |- |}
